indimail-mta (2.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * quoted svctool arguments and save install time arguments in variables/.options file
  * update_tmprsadh, svctool, spec files, debian postinst, postrm - updated certificate location to sysconfdir/certs
  * qmail-smtpd, qmail-remote - Env variable CERTDIR to override /etc/indimail/control for certificate location
  * Permissions of supervise directory changed to onwer root:indimail 750 for services using MAXDAEMONS
  * renamed qmail-spamfifo service to qmail-logfifo
  * added upgrade script upgrade.sh, local_upgrade.sh
  * update_tmprsadh - added rsa2048.pem, dh2048.pem
  * ucspi-tcp - control_readline() did not use CONTROLDIR. Caused problem with qmail_smtpd.so plugin which used the same symbol and was unable to load control files.
  * fixed conf_dir variable getting clobbered by qmail-logfifo service creation.
  * create tlsservermethod control file in svctool --config=qmail
  * renamed functions in ucspi-tcp (rblsmtpd.so) to avoid duplicate symbols with qmail_smtpd.so
  * use RTLD_DEEPBIND (if present) in load_shared.c to avoid duplicate symbols when loading multiple shared libs
  * set DEFAULT_DOMAIN in qmail-send.25/variables as the hostname to handle double bounces better
  * qmail-todo, qmail-send - display null email address as <> in log_stat()
  * svctool --config=qmail - set envnoathost, defaulthost = hostname 
  * local_upgrade.sh - fix DEFAULT_HOST, QMAILDEFAULTHOST, envnoathost, defaulthost settings
  * svctool - MRTG graphs, added --mrtg option
  * local_upgrade.sh added FIFODIR env variable
  * replace dlopen() with dlmopen to keep tcpserver namespace private
  * added dlnamespace for using dlmopen()
  * tcpserver.c, prot.c - Changed data types for uid, gid to uid_t, gid_t
  * Bug with dlmopen(), glibc wrappers for setgroups, setgid, setuid - use syscall for setgroups, setgid, setuid
  * tcpserver - execute tcpserver_plugin after shedding root privileges
  * indimail-mta.postinst.in, indimail-mta.spec - upgraded softmem to 536870912
  * svctool - Fixed couriersslcache path
  * dlnamespace.c - added comments, replace back ':' character removed before string comparision
  * qmail-remote.c - fixed tls_quit() function. Avoid mixed usage of tls_quit() and quit() functions
  * qmail-remote.c, rrt.c - renamed ONTRANSIENT_REMOTE to ONTEMPORARY_REMOTE
  * qmail-rspawn.c Unset QMAILLOCAL in parent & not in child after vfork
  * perms of /etc/indimail and subdirectory changed to 2775
  * qmail-remote.c - use SMTPS if env variable SMTPS is set
  * qmail-queue.c - fixed envheader. variable x renamed to field_len and initialized to prevent skipping.
  * fixed sysconfdir and sysconfdir subdir permissions
  * use #ifdef HASDLMOPEN to use dlmopen() if present
  * tcpserver_plugin.c - use PLUGINn_DIR variable to change directory independent of PLUGINn_init env variable
  * create queue base directory in setup
  * report programs moved to libexecdir
  * surblqueue - fixed qmail-multi path
  * fixed search using hsearch in qmail-greyd.c
  * tcpserver - load_shared.c - print lmid only during reload
  * moved qmail-greyd, greydaemon, surblfilter, surbqueue to /usr/sbin
  * use lockfile .svlock in service directory to prevent multiple svscan to run on a service directory
  * dlnamespace.c, tcpserver_plugin.c, load_shared.c, pathexec_env.c added code to get namespace of shared libraries using env variables / envp variable
  * qmailctl.sh - added multilog rotate command
  * indimail-mta - install crontab entries for indimail-mta
  * qmail-smtpd - Updated documentation on LOGFILTER
  * qmail-smtpd - renamed LOGFILTER_FD to LOGFD
  * shutdown indimail service in preun
  * (rpm, debian) - use svok to figure out if service is up
  * svctool - fixed inverted cname-lookup
  * (rpm, debian) - removed duplicate calls to shutdown indimail service
  * (rpm, debian) - use sed to edit inittab
  * added svctool man page
  * fixed sysconfdir variable in debian scripts
  * OSX indimail.plist - fixed svscanboot path
  * fixed DESTDIR in qmail-1.03, ucspi-tcp-1.03 Makefile, setup.c
  * fixed tlsclientmethod path in qmail-remote
  * cleanq.c - refactored code. added checks for safety
  * setup.c, instcheck.c - added logdir

 -- Manvendra Bhangui <manvendra@indimail.org>  Fri, 05 May 2017 20:44:55 +0530
